        <div class="body">
            <p>Your change will cause trouble. The goal is to test existence of row field. Null is a value, so we can switch for isset().</p>

<p>Sample: a table for users with a column last_visited. A null value means that the user never logged. If you write :</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
isset($users-&gt;last_visited);
</code></pre>

<p>The column exists, and the value is null.</p>

